Hiking spots in Seattle with their difficulty level

In this graph, I wanted to explore different hiking routes. I enjoy hiking and have explored many trails outside of Seattle and in PNW but I think I have failed to explore trails within Seattle area. To explore different trails in Seattle, I used the trail dataset released by Seattle Parks and Recreation(SPR). I mapped different trails maintained by SPR on top of base map of Seattle. First I wanted the layer map to be muted so we can focus on the information pop up. I first added map cluster so we can see total number of trails in particular locations like in Magnusun Park or Discover Park. I also encoded the map with icons of person walking to indicate they are walkable place. I also encoded these icones with colors based on the intensity of hike: Flat, Gradual, moderate and Steep.I also added legend to these colors so viewers can map the intesity of hike with colors they see on the icons. I also added tool tip with the name of the park and type. Type indicates what kind of trail it is. For example it lists, if the trail bank, gravel, soil, stairs etc so that hikers can prepare their clothes and shoes accordingly. While adding trail name would have been ideal, the information was not available in the SPR database, so I added park name which was the only idenfication information available.
